-- Voeckler Wins Tour de France Mountain Stage; Wiggins Leads
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-07-18T15:23:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/europcar-s-thomas-voeckler-wins-mountain-stage-of-tour-de-france.html
Thomas Voeckler  of Europcar won the
16th stage of the Tour de France with a breakaway in the
Pyrenees mountains.  The Frenchman finished the 197-kilometer (122-mile) course
over the Tourmalet and three other climbs in 5 hours, 35 minutes
and 2 seconds. Chris Anker Sorensen of Saxo Bank finished
second.  Bradley Wiggins of Britain kept his lead in the overall
tour, finishing with second-placed teammate Chris Froome and
third-placed Vincenzo Nibali of Liquigas as they crossed the
line together, 7 minutes, 12 seconds behind Voeckler. Last
yearâ€™s winner  Cadel Evans  lost time on the top three, and fell
three places to seventh after the stage between Pau and
Bagneres-de-Luchon.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
